{"title":"Project Management Plan (PMP)","markdown":{"headingText":"Project Management Plan (PMP)","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n## Purpose of the PMP\n\nThis Project Management Plan (PMP) defines **how the project will be executed,\nmonitored, controlled, and closed**, in alignment with:\n\n- Approved Project Charter\n- Strategy & Governance (Value Stream, OKRs, KPIs)\n- Business Case\n- Scope Baseline (Scope Statement, WBS, WBS Dictionary)\n- Stakeholder Register\n- Requirements Specification\n\nThe PMP is the **authoritative execution reference** for the project.\n\n---\n\n## Project Governance Overview\n\n### Governance Model\n\n- **Ecology-first governance**: ecological KPIs take precedence\n- **Stage-Gate decision model** based on KPI thresholds\n- **Human-in-the-loop** mandatory for all ecological decisions\n\n### Decision Authorities\n\n| Decision Type | Authority |\n|--------------|-----------|\n| Strategic Direction | Sponsor (NOAA / SUB) |\n| Ecological Acceptance | Environmental SME Lead |\n| Technical Decisions | Data Science Lead |\n| Delivery & Control | Project Manager |\n\n---\n\n## Scope Management Plan\n\n- Scope is defined by the **Scope Baseline**\n- No work outside approved WBS is permitted\n- Scope changes require:\n  - Formal Change Request\n  - Impact analysis (ecological, schedule, cost)\n  - Sponsor approval\n\n---\n\n## Schedule Management Plan\n\n- Schedule derived directly from WBS\n- Milestone-driven planning\n- Stage-Gates act as **hard control points**\n- Ecological validation tasks are non-compressible\n\n---\n\n## Cost Management Plan\n\n- Cost categories:\n  - Personnel (Data Science, Engineering, SMEs)\n  - Compute & storage\n  - Governance & validation effort\n- Contingency reserves maintained for annotation uncertainty\n- Cost performance reviewed at Stage-Gates\n\n---\n\n## Quality Management Plan (Integrated)\n\n### Quality Objectives\n- Protect benthic-relevant data\n- Maintain ecological confidence\n- Ensure reproducibility and auditability\n\n### Quality Control\n- KPI-3 (Ecological Data Protection Index) is mandatory\n- SME validation is required for acceptance\n- Documentation of limitations is compulsory\n\n---\n\n## Resource Management Plan\n\n| Role | Responsibility |\n|-----|----------------|\n| Project Manager | Coordination and control |\n| Product Owner | OKR ownership |\n| Environmental SMEs | Ecological validation |\n| Data Science Team | Model development |\n| Data Engineering Team | Pipeline & assets |\n\n---\n\n## Communication Management Plan\n\n| Stakeholder | Information | Frequency |\n|------------|-------------|-----------|\n| Sponsor | Status & risks | Monthly / Gates |\n| SMEs | Validation results | Weekly |\n| PO & PM | Delivery alignment | ≥ 2× per week |\n| Team | Execution updates | Weekly |\n\n---\n\n## Risk Management Plan\n\n- Risk Register maintained and reviewed continuously\n- Ecological risks prioritized\n- Any degradation of KPI-3 triggers escalation\n\n---\n\n## Change Management Plan\n\n- Formal Change Control Log maintained\n- All changes assessed for ecological impact\n- Unauthorized scope changes prohibited\n\n---\n\n## Procurement Management Plan\n\n- Only license-compliant AI frameworks\n- Internal infrastructure preferred\n- External procurement subject to Petrobras rules\n\n---\n\n## Stakeholder Engagement Plan\n\n- Engagement strategies derived from Stakeholder Register\n- Environmental SMEs engaged continuously\n- Sponsor involved at all Stage-Gates\n\n---\n\n## Integration with OKRs, KPIs and Stage-Gates\n\n- OKR 2.1 defines value\n- KPIs define measurement\n- Stage-Gates define control\n- PMP defines execution\n\n---\n\n## Baseline Management\n\nBaselines maintained:\n- Scope Baseline\n- Schedule Baseline (to be approved)\n- Cost Baseline (to be approved)\n\nChanges to baselines require Sponsor approval.\n\n---\n\n## Project Closure Criteria\n\n- MVP ecological acceptance achieved\n- KPIs validated\n- Assets versioned and stored\n- Lessons learned documented\n- Sponsor sign-off\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":true,"code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":[],"notebook-links":true,"format-links":["html","pdf"]},"pandoc":{"standalone":true,"wrap":"none","default-image-extension":"png","to":"html","metadata-files":["../location/pt.yml"],"toc":true,"css":["../styles.css"],"html-math-method":"mathjax","embed-resources":true,"output-file":"pmp.html"},"language":{"toc-title-document":"Índice","toc-title-website":"Nesta página","related-formats-title":"Outros formatos","related-notebooks-title":"Notebooks","source-notebooks-prefix":"Fonte","other-links-title":"Outros Links","code-links-title":"Ligações de código","launch-dev-container-title":"Iniciar Dev Container","launch-binder-title":"Iniciar Binder","article-notebook-label":"